                                        <b>Additional Services (optional):</b><br><br>
                                        <b><i>Payment Protection Plan</i></b> (PPP) is a plan that protects NEAC applicants from any type of financial losses that may occur during the processing of their NCLEX Eligibility Application and or Credential Evaluation Services based on the plan chosen. It has been reported by some NCLEX applicants that some State Board of Nursing have lost their payments and don't want to take any responsibility of it. This has been the case even if the applicant has provided a proof of payment. In this type of situation applicant can actually take his or her complaints to Board's management however usually it is very difficult or get hold of someone and wait for any reply from the management in a timely manner. It is also possible that money draft may be lost by the carrier. Either way the applicant is in a position to make another payment in the same amount, pay the money draft assistance fee and spend additional express mailing fee to send the payment to the Board of Nursing again. This will also slow down the application process. Even though this type of problem does not take place very often, NEAC's Payment Protection Plan protects applicants from possible losses and gives peace of mind. With this Payment Protection Plan, applicants will be protected up to P40,000 in losses. Which means in case of any of those above described incidents occur NEAC will be the one making the necessary payments to the related departments immediately so that the application can be filed successfully and the processing continues in full speed. In the meantime, NEAC will be communicating to the related departments to recover the lost payment(s) if recoverable. In case third party organizations who received the payment agree to credit or refund any overpayments, the refund will be sent directly to the applicant. When the applicant receives a refund, he or she agrees to pay it back to NEAC within 7 working days. <br><br>
